@node Sonstiges "PacMan.Guide: by the way..."
@prev Anmerkungen
@next News

I thought it might be interesting to write down a speed comparison between
fast and slow crunchers.
Crunching a 49 KB program with StoneCracker 3.10 took 2.5 seconds, Master
Cruncher 3.0 needed 21 minutes for the same file, that means, it took
500 times longer than StoneCracker (the result was a file of 23 KB size;
StoneCracker produced a file of 25.5 KB)...
@endnode

