@node V120 "PacMan.Guide: Changes in version 1.20"
@next News
@prev V119

CrList: tested Mega Cruncher 1.2 R / TurboSqueezer 8.0.

Code optimized a bit.

A bug was fixed that occured when using the -Y option. This time, it
wasn't only my fault :^) (See also: OtherStuff/SCTest.Txt).

Since crunching of very large files with 68000-Amigas costs lots of time,
I did now add a break function. I've been too lazy before. :^)
A running crunch process can now be stopped immediately by a BREAK signal
(Ctrl.-C), but this is only possible DURING CRUNCHING itself.
At the same way a directory view now may be terminated.
Note again that a decrunch procedure can't be stopped yet.

All dox now available in AmigaGuide format. 
To prevent myself from boring work, the ASCII dox will be made off the
Guide docs (quickly). That means, if I was you, I'd prefer the AmigaGuide
version... :^)

For da ASCII-freax I have extracted the program history from the textfile.

Some poor kinda guy who's still running his Amiga under KickStart 1.2
complained about PacMan requiring Kick 1.3. I didn't find a reason for
this, so I changed it. You may now run PacMan with Kick 1.2 (is there any-
body else left in the galaxy still using Kick 1.2 ?)

Added AmigaOS compatible Version number. PacMan's version number may now
be displayed using the Version command.
Be aware of Fakes ! Some kids have fun on overwriting strings inside of
foreign programs using a file monitor. Even strings including version
numbers in ASCII coded form are prefered parts for those dudes (who mostly
don't know much more about computers).
The real version number which is displayed with every PacMan call, was
protected (encrypted) against such kinda primitive attack. :^)

PacMan now adds a KillSys loader to absolute coded files, if the decrunch
address is lower than $20000. Without this measure, the decrunched pro-
gram would crash after loading, because the memory area below approx.
$20000 is filled with important data belonging to the operating system.

Because of PowerPacker2.3_MasterMode files won't be decrunched correctly,
I added a safety check which ALWAYS prevents the source file from deletion
after depacking.

Option -M is new. By passing a percent value, you may now determine a mi-
nimum crunch efficiency. That means: files crunched with less than the
given percentage gain will no longer be changed.
The default minimum value equals 15 percent.

From now on PacMan checks if it was launched from Workbench, because I saw
a dude who couldn't let it be. In this case PacMan quits immediately.

Finally, I added ReqTools.library again to the archive, because it even
has become bigger since the Amigaguide files were added...
@endnode

@node V119 "PacMan.Guide: Changes in version 1.19"
@next V120
@prev V118

PowerPacker 2.3a/2.3b "Master Mode" files will be identified now (but NOT
displayed in QuickView mode).
Attention ! Unpacking PowerPacker 2.3a/2.3b MM files will result in a
trashed file (by now). Seems that PowerPacker 3.0b MM files will be cor-
rectly decrunched.

That's all this time, sorry. I didn't have much time for updating in the
last weeks before CeBit party... :^)
@endnode

@node V118 "PacMan.Guide: Changes in version 1.18"
@next V119
@prev V117

Included the new decrunch.library V 35.237. This time, it wasn't expanded
by new cruncher types. Only the recognization of some CrunchMania files
was improved. Some CrunchMania names have been changed again. See also
PacMan.CrList.

Again a little text output bug (V 1.17) tickled in. After the "Loading..."
message a (mysterious :^) number was typed. This one was built-in for
testing the -K option. I just forgot to remove that...

Seems that nobody noticed that PacMan crashed after decrunching a file, if
the destination file save failed. Bug removed. :^)

Added -V option. See crunch/decrunch opts.

CrList: tested HQC Cruncher 2.0, Master Cruncher 3.0, PackIt 1.0 R/D,
Spike Cruncher 1.5, StoneCracker 3.00 D/4.00 R/D, Titanics Cruncher 1.1.

PowerPacker 3.0b "Master Mode" files are recognized now. PacMan informs
you if it's working on such kinda files (not in QuickView mode).

PacMan now sets the DOS Return_Code to zero when finishing. If anything
went wrong while running, the AmigaDOS Return_Code will be set to 20
(RETURN_FAIL). See also: examples.

I decided to remove the reqtools.library from the PacMan archive now,
because everyone's got it and it's only used for password crunch/decrunch.
This makes the PacMan archive smaller.
@endnode

@node V117 "PacMan.Guide: Changes in version 1.17"
@next V118
@prev V116

In View mode now paths can be specified, too. These will then be complete-
ly checked (but not recursively yet). Therefor, a QuickView mode will be
activated, which saves space in the text display (see also View opts).

Added opts H, Q and U (everyone as additional opt for the View mode).

PacMan now displays the crunch efficiencies of every PowerPacker file,
which means: PP-executables, too (PP 2.xx - PP 4.0).

CrList: TurtleSmasher 2.00 D checked.
        StoneCracker 3.10 D checked.

Added K option.

Since a few weeks, there's an archive going around which is named
"PacMa133.lha".
This archive contains PacMan V 1.13 (the one with the small text output
bug...smile...see also V 1.14).
A version 1.33 obviously does not exist yet.
Seems that some dude mistook the version number while repacking the
archive. -Or someone highly needed 20 KB of file creditz...:^)
@endnode

@node V116 "PacMan.Guide: Changes in version 1.16"
@next V117
@prev V115

CrList: Checked Imploder 1.0.
        Checked the 4 new CrunchMania file types.

Added new ReqTools.library (Kick 2.0) V 38.1022.

Added new Decrunch.library V 35.213.
The Decrunch.library now recognizes 93 different types of crunched files.
@endnode

@node V115 "PacMan.Guide: Changes in version 1.15"
